18
00:01:04,110 --> 00:01:05,960
The television.

19
00:01:05,960 --> 00:01:09,140
TV was coming into the homes of all the children.

20
00:01:09,140 --> 00:01:12,770
Adults were worried that kids were going to learn these violent behaviors watching &quot;The

21
00:01:12,770 --> 00:01:16,690
Lone Ranger&quot;, and carry them out in real life.

22
00:01:16,690 --> 00:01:20,670
These kinds of arguments still happen today on the topic of things like violent video

23
00:01:20,670 --> 00:01:22,490
games or movies.

24
00:01:22,490 --> 00:01:23,930
It&#39;s still a concern.

25
00:01:23,930 --> 00:01:28,409
What Bandura’s experiment did very nicely, though, is show that children can imitate,

26
00:01:28,409 --> 00:01:31,400
and that they can embellish and expand upon what they see.

27
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:36,060
It doesn&#39;t necessarily show that violent video games and TV is bad for children, but that

28
00:01:36,060 --> 00:01:37,320
